{"lemma":"مِنْسَأَةٍ","slug":"مِنْسَأَةٍ","root":"ن.س.#","root_slug":"ن-س-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-س-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39688","n39689"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D9%86%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"staff, crook, crosier; wand, sceptre"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَسَأَ (nasaʔa, “to postpone”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Hebrew מִשְׁעֵנָה (mišʿēnā, “staff”)."},"ipa":["/min.sa.ʔa/","/man.sa.ʔa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39688","headword_ar":"مَنْسَاَةٌ","root":"nsA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Silapu Alr~aHimi mavoraApN fiY AlmaAli","text_ar":"صِلَةُ الرَّحِمِ مَثْرَاةٌ فِى المَالِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manosaA^apN fiY AlA^avari","text_ar":"مَنْسَاَةٌ فِى الاَثَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Union with kindred is a means of multiplying wealth, a means of prolonging one's memorial"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA, from a trad.)       -A2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minosaA^apN","text_ar":"مِنْسَاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n39689","headword_ar":"مِنْسَاَةٌ","root":"nsA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manosaA^apN","text_ar":"مَنْسَاَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and also without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because a beast is urged or driven with it: (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pastor's great staff."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) For"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minosaA^atahu","text_ar":"مِنْسَاَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, xxxiv. 13, some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino saA^atihi","text_ar":"مِنْ سَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e. “ from, or of, the end of his staff; ”"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sA^ap","text_ar":"ساَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally signifying the “ bent part at each end of a bow; ” (Fr, TA, &c.;) and being here used tropically. (TA.) This reading is disapproved by the author of the K. but is supported by good authorities. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}